            <h3 id="pos-form-functioning">4.2) POS form functioning</h3>
            
            <h4>4.2.1. Transaction start</h4>
            <h5>A. Location selection</h5>
            <p>A menu at the top of the page displays the current location (e.g., <em>Senteur & Vitalit√©</em>), which is crucial in a multi-store environment. It indicates where the operation is recorded and affects <strong>inventory movements to this location.</strong></p>
            
            <h5>B. Sale date and time</h5>
            <p>Dynamic display of timestamp to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Facilitate real-time sales tracking,</li>
                <li>Precisely date each transaction.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>4.2.2. Customer identification</h4>
            <p>The system defaults to an anonymous customer ("Walk-in customer"). A (+) button allows manually adding a new customer or selecting an existing one.</p>
            <p><strong>Advantage:</strong> if a customer is identified, the sale will be linked to their account for better tracking (purchase history, credit, loyalty).</p>
            
            <h4>4.2.3. Product addition</h4>
            <p>The interface offers several ways to add items to the cart:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>By entering the name, product code, or barcode scan,</li>
                <li>Or via direct selection from the visual catalog on the right.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Each added product appears in an interactive table containing:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Product name,</li>
                <li>Quantity to sell (modifiable),</li>
                <li>Unit price and subtotal,</li>
