            <h2 id="import-sales">12) Import sales</h2>
            
            <h3 id="import-general-presentation">12.1) General presentation</h3>
            <p>The <strong>Import Sales</strong> functionality allows users to <strong>bulk load sales data</strong> from an external file (CSV or Excel), rather than entering them manually one by one. It's an essential tool in the following contexts:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Data migration from an old system,</li>
                <li>Integration of sales from another channel (e-commerce, ERP, etc.),</li>
                <li>Catch-up of historical entries,</li>
                <li>Automation of regular processes.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3 id="import-objectives">12.2) Objectives</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Save time when entering multiple sales.</li>
                <li>Avoid <strong>manual errors</strong> of duplication or omission.</li>
                <li>Ensure <strong>smooth integration</strong> between different data sources.</li>
                <li>Enable <strong>quick updates to the sales database.</strong></li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3 id="import-interface-steps">12.3) Interface and import steps</h3>
            <p>The module follows a multi-step guided process, ensuring reliable and well-structured imports.</p>
            
            <h4>A. Template download</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Users can download a <strong>CSV or Excel template with the</strong> <strong>expected columns</strong> (reference, customer, date, products, quantities, amounts, payment status, etc.).</li>
                <li>This template is provided to standardize the format of data to be imported.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>B. File upload</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Once the template is completed, the user selects the file to import.</li>
                <li>The system verifies data validity: duplicates, incorrect format, missing fields, encoding errors (e.g.: wrong separator).</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>C. Import preview</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Before final validation, users can preview <strong>detected sales.</strong></li>
                <li>Erroneous lines are highlighted with clear error messages for correction.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>D. Final import</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Once the file is validated, sales are integrated into the database, appear in the sales list, and trigger:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Stock movements,</li>
                        <li>Customer updates,</li>
                        <li>Report generation.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>E) Download</h4>
            <p>Once the import is complete, you can download the file and review it to verify all updates were properly applied.</p>
            <p>This interface also provides instructions to follow for successful imports.</p>
            
